                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.C2/230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-14T11:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 14, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 14—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Messrs. Brown Scott and Reeves have handed me the following text for
                    transmission to the Department: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In compliance with the Department’s telegram of May 13th, we hasten to
                            state that we shall refrain from introducing the plan. We avail
                            ourselves of the opportunity of expressing our appreciation of the
                            courteous language in which the Department’s instruction is
                            couched.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
